properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 20 at 2:35AM PST until February 20 at 3:00PM PST by NWS Hanford CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...East to southeast winds 15 to 25 mph with gusts up to 45
mph expected.

* WHERE...Kern county mountains...specifically the valley facing
slopes of the Tehachapi mountains as well as east to west
oriented canyons and passes.

* WHEN...From 8 AM this morning to 3 PM PST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree
limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
Difficulty driving especially for high profile vehicles such as
camper and tractor trailers.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Highways affected include I-5 over the
Grapevine and Highway 58 through Tehachapi Pass.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 8 AM THIS MORNING TO 3 PM PST THIS AFTERNOON
